The paper focuses on a buffer management algorithm for packet routing, which is a common problem in computer networks. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). However, the paper specifically deals with the design and analysis of an algorithm, which is more closely related to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which could fall under Information Theory (cs.IT), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), or Machine Learning (cs.LG).
